nal screening determination after all inclusion and exclusion criteria are reviewed.\\\" data_type: \\\"boolean\\\" required: null unit: null range: null options: [] visible_when: null required_when: null calculation: null source_refs: - locator: \\\"Flow diagram, page 3; Randomisation, allocation concealment and blinding, page 4\\\" confidence: \\\"medium\\\" notes: - \\\"The field is proposed as a manually confirmed determination because the renderer contract does not support a safe Boolean eligibility calculation.\\\" inference: kind: \\\"inferred_supporting_field\\\" rationale: \\\"The protocol explicitly transitions eligible screened patients to randomisation, which directly implies a final determination.\\\" confidence_percent: 95 coding: status: \\\"unresolved\\\" rationale: \\\"Official CDASHIG v2.1 mapping review completed; specialist candidate selection remains pending.\\\" unresolved_items: - id: \\\"U-001\\\" severity: \\\"warning\\\" question: \\\"Which single candidate form should be generated first?\\\" affected_concepts: - \\\"selected_form\\\" source_refs: - locator: \\\"Protocol-wide candidate-form inventory, pages 2-6\\\" resolution: \\\"The user selected screening-eligibility. This records form selection only and is not Gate A approval.\\\" resolved_by: \\\"user\\\" resolved_at: \\\"2026-07-21T06:57:16.5844044Z\\\" - id: \\\"U-002\\\" severity: \\\"warning\\\" question: \\\"What protocol version and protocol date should be recorded? The journal publication year and online publication date are not labelled as the protocol version/date.\\\" affected_concepts: - \\\"source.protocol_version\\\" - \\\"source.protocol_date\\\" source_refs: - locator: \\\"Article header, page 1\\\" resolution: null resolved_by: null resolved_at: null - id: \\\"U-003\\\" severity: \\\"blocking\\\" question: \\\"For the selected form, which fields are mandatory? The protocol generally does not state field-level requiredness.\\\" affected_concepts: - \\\"selected_form.fields.required\\\" source_refs: - locator: \\\"Outcome assessment and study examination procedures, pages 4-6\\\" resolution: \\\"The user approved the Gate A proposal: all core screening fields are required; investigator_unsuitable_reason is conditionally required when exc16 is Y; calculated BMI is read-only and is not independently required.\\\" resolved_by: \\\"user decision in Codex task\\\" resolved_at: \\\"2026-07-21\\\" - id: \\\"U-004\\\" severity: \\\"blocking\\\" question: \\\"For the selected form, confirm the data types, units, precision, and edit-check ranges that the protocol does not explicitly define.\\\" affected_concepts: - \\\"selected_form.fields.data_type\\\" - \\\"selected_form.fields.unit\\\" - \\\"selected_form.fields.range\\\" source_refs: - locator: \\\"Outcome and procedure descriptions, pages 4-6\\\" resolution: \\\"The user approved the proposed data types, protocol units and threshold consistency checks. Unstated plausible-data ranges and precision remain unset; BMI displays two decimal places per the user's implementation request.\\\" resolved_by: \\\"user decision in Codex task\\\" resolved_at: \\\"2026-07-21\\\" - id: \\\"U-005\\\" severity: \\\"warning\\\" question: \\\"At which visits are lung function and ECG performed? They are exceptions to the general baseline/3/6/12-month schedule, but the alternative schedule is not stated.\\\" affected_concepts: - \\\"lung_function.visit_schedule\\\" - \\\"ecg.visit_schedule\\\" source_refs: - locator: \\\"Study examination procedures, page 5\\\" resolution: null resolved_by: null resolved_at: null - id: \\\"U-006\\\" severity: \\\"blocking\\\" question: \\\"Should MoCA and MMSE be represented as total scores only, or should licensed item-level instruments be supplied separately? The protocol does not reproduce the item-level forms.\\\" affected_concepts: - \\\"moca\\\" - \\\"mmse\\\" source_refs: - locator: \\\"Basic characteristics and primary/secondary endpoints, page 4\\\" resolution: \\\"T